      validity: 'A decision rule for children with CSF pleocytosis; a score of 0 carries a very high negative predictive value but does not apply to infants <=28 days, the critically ill, or those pretreated with antibiotics, and never overrides clinical judgment.',
      source: 'Nigrovic LE, Kuppermann N, Macias CG, et al. Clinical prediction rule for identifying children with cerebrospinal fluid pleocytosis at very low risk of bacterial meningitis. JAMA. 2007;297(1):52-60.',
